<h2>
    Fishing Regulations and License Requirements
</h2>
<h3>
    Harvest vs. Catch-and-Release Rules
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        Many steelhead must be released unless marked with a clipped adipose fin (indicating hatchery origin).
    </li>
    <li>
        Wild steelhead are <strong>protected</strong> and must be handled with care.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    Tagging, Size, and Gear Limits
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        Oregon Angling License + Combined Angling Tag required
    </li>
    <li>
        Barbless hooks in some areas
    </li>
    <li>
        Daily catch limit: usually 2 hatchery steelhead (check ODFW updates)
    </li>
</ul>
